The paper deals with lower bounds for the number of Pareto optimal solutions in multi-criteria optimization problems, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), and network economics (cs.NE). The use of smoothed analysis also suggests a connection to randomized algorithms and probabilistic analysis, which are common in these sub-categories.
